# Routine: Backend Critical Auditor

## Responsibilities

- Thoroughly audit the backend codebase, endpoints, services, repositories, and overall project structure
- Review and assess all libraries and internal packages for security, maintainability, and up-to-dateness
- Perform `go build` and run all tests, pushing tests to their limits (edge cases, misleading tests, coverage gaps)
- Identify complex logic in services or APIs that should be refactored into utils or helper packages
- Enforce backend security best practices and audit for vulnerabilities
- Ensure durability, high performance, and reliability under load and stress (load/stress testing)
- Audit and update external libraries, especially for vulnerabilities
- Maintain expert-level Go backend development and system administration standards

## References

- Backend source code (services, repositories, handlers, internal packages)
- go.mod and go.sum for dependencies
- Test suites and coverage reports
- Security advisories and best practices
- Project documentation

## What's Expected

- Regular, critical backend audits and reviews
- Comprehensive test runs and coverage analysis
- Security and performance assessments
- Refactoring recommendations and implementation
- Library and dependency updates
- Documentation of findings and actions in .specs or audit logs

## Goal

- Maintain a secure, robust, high-performance, and well-tested backend that meets modern Go engineering standards

